So one part of your retina can
be sort of electrically and

00:03:10.690 --> 00:03:13.830
chemically setting its dynamic
range at one place, and

00:03:13.830 --> 00:03:16.320
another part is at another
place simultaneously.

00:03:16.320 --> 00:03:19.900
So the part that's looking at
the bright window in the church

00:03:19.900 --> 00:03:21.390
is operating at one place.

00:03:21.390 --> 00:03:24.950
The part that's op, that's looking
at the the darker part, it,

00:03:24.950 --> 00:03:27.650
it, it's doing its center-surround
on a darker area, but

00:03:27.650 --> 00:03:30.280
it's looking at those
relative contrasts.

